rait that is at once a model of fine narrative history and an example of how one can walk the intellectual tightrope between 'reporting one's findings' and offering judgements about them."-Peter I. Rose, Contemporary Sociology  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package Archive 1960-1989z978311066784440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226237992423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226237992.jpg  a978-3-11-066784-4  UChP eBook-Package Archive 1960-1989c1960d1989  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles